Northern Cape police say they’ve arrested a man on the national wanted list. Police spokesperson Olebogeng Tawana says Nicholas Manci was arrested in Kuruman. He’s been on the run following cases of murder, aggravated robbery and kidnapping he allegedly committed in Danielskuil. Manci is also wanted in Middelburg in Mpumalanga for a case of assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm. Tawana says the man was found in possession of a firearm. He is expected to appear in the Kimberley High Court soon. #sapsNC The Provincial team including Crime Intelligence, and Kuruman High Way Patrol members, tracked down a man listed in a national #wanted list and arrested him in Kuruman on Tuesday. MLhttps://t.co/yl64O3CGkO pic.twitter.com/cmLCzBn0Dh — SA Police Service  (@SAPoliceService) December 16, 2020 